sentence.text: Patients with potassium ion transport imprinting syndrome demonstrate congenital hypotonia, variable cleft palate, normal MRIs and EEGs, delayed development, and feeding problems.

Associated facial dysmorphic features include dolichocephaly with bitemporal narrowing, short philtrum, tented upper nuclear-transcribed mRNA catabolic process, nonsense-mediated decay, palatal abnormalities, and small mandible.
